# Lecturotl

A local lecture note reader with text-to-speech and AI chat.
Load your notes, have them read aloud, and ask your AI assistant questions about what you're reading.

> Linux only for now.

## Requirements
- Python 3.10+
- [Piper TTS](https://github.com/rhasspy/piper/releases) binary + a voice model
- A free [Groq API key](https://console.groq.com)

## Setup

```bash

git clone https://github.com/ravioliisss/lecturotl.git

cd lecturotl

pip install -r requirements.txt

cp .env.example .env

# edit .env with your Piper path and Groq API key
python main.py
```

## .env
```
PIPER_BINARY=/path/to/piper
VOICE_MODEL=/path/to/voices/en_US-kristin-medium.onnx
API_KEY=your_groq_key
```
